content:
Get More from Salesforce Maps with an Enhanced User Experience

Deliver dramatic performance improvements while plotting high-volume data including ArcGIS Online layers and complex shape layers when you switch to the new framework in Salesforce Maps. And give your reps access to a modern and robust list view experience.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions on desktops.

When: Expect the new Salesforce Maps framework by or shortly after the general availability of Summer ’24.

FEATURE AREA	ENHANCED FRAMEWORK BENEFITS

The map
Plot extensive, subscription-free data by using ArcGIS Living Atlas of the World, from Esri. For example, plot weather events and their historical paths, demographics, and utility and agricultural infrastructures.
Identify recent traffic events such as road closures, accidents, and construction areas.
Page between neighboring markers and shape layers that overlap.

List views
Perform actions on rows within any tab in list views. For example, add records to campaigns, change record owners, and set proximity centers based on record addresses.
Refine list views continuously instead of having to create ones that include your changes.

Shape drawing functions
When your reps edit drawn shapes, they’re moveable to other areas on the map.
Set the center in shapes for travel time, travel distance, and circular boundaries by address or by latitude and longitude coordinates. As your reps enter addresses, Salesforce Maps suggests addresses with an auto-complete feature.

Appearance
The enhanced framework adds a refreshed and functional style for marker pop-ups, shape drawing features, list views, and marker clusters.

How: To experience the new framework, open Salesforce Maps configuration, click Settings, and then select Enhanced User Experience.
title: Enhanced Salesforce Maps User Experience
